text: Keken-Vasilyevka () is a rural locality (a selo) in Kozhay-Semyonovsky Selsoviet, Miyakinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 303 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 15 km from Kirgiz-Miyaki, 10 km from Kozhay-Semyonovka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Miyakinsky District
title: Keken-Vasilyevka
